"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"np.sinc() function returns sin(pi*x)/(pi*x) at x=0, np.sinc() is defined to be 1. However, np.sinc() does not return exactly 0 at x=1. The sinc function is not exactly 0 at x=1 due to floating point precision issues. Therefore, the assertion sinc_result[1] == 0 will fail.\", \"patch\": \"7c7\\n< assert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n---\\n> assert np.isclose(sinc_result[0], 1), \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n8c8\\n< assert sinc_result[1] == 0, \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\\n---\\n> assert np.isclose(sinc_result[1], np.sinc(1)), \\\"Results not equal to np.sinc(1)\\\"\"}"